A claim circulating around the internet claiming that a virus called the &#8220;Dance of Hillary&#8221; will ruin your phone is fake. JOHANNESBURG A claim circulating around the internet claiming that a virus called the Dance of Hillary will ruin your phone is fake.According to Morning News USA there is no mobile phone virus threat like the one described. In fact, the message is just a mutated version of the earlier Dance of the Pope virus hoax.The message was created to act as a scare tactic by pranksters. This comes after false accounts of 702, the Sunday Times and the Huffington Post emerged over the weekend.A number of false posts appeared on Twitter with inaccurate and misleading information.This included stories about Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan and others.